Collections:
	Collections is an architecture to store, retrieve, manipulate, and process groups of objects efficiently.
	Collection is a concept of storing multiple data into a single variable	based on some condition.
	Array is size fixed while creation whereas collection may grows or shrinks( dynamic in size).
	
	
Iterable
   |
Collection
   ├── List --> ArrayList,LinkedList,Vector(legacy),Stack(legacy)
   ├── Set  --> HashSet,LinkedHashSet,TreeSet
   └── Queue


Map  (separate hierarchy)  -->HashMap,LinkedHashMap,TreeMap,HashTable(legacy)